#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:-1
msgid ""
"A guide to distinguish the roles and responsibilities associated with "
"managing the Spack Packages repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:12
msgid "Packaging Roles and Responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:14
msgid ""
"There are four roles related to `Spack Package <https://github.com/spack/"
"spack-packages>`_ repository Pull Requests (PRs):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:16
msgid ":ref:`package-contributors`,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:17
msgid ":ref:`package-reviewers`,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:18
msgid ":ref:`package-maintainers`, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:19
msgid ":ref:`committers`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:21
msgid ""
"One person can assume multiple roles (e.g., a Package Contributor may also "
"be a Maintainer; a Package Reviewer may also be a Committer). This section "
"defines and describes the responsibilities of each role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:27
msgid "Package Contributors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:29
msgid ""
"Contributors submit changes to packages through PRs `Spack Package <https://"
"github.com/spack/spack-packages>`_ repository Pull Requests (PRs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:31
msgid ""
"As a Contributor, you are **expected** to test your changes on **at least "
"one platform** outside of Spack’s Continuous Integration (CI) checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:35
msgid ""
"We also ask that you include the output from ``spack debug report`` from the "
"platform you used to facilitate PR reviews."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:40
msgid "Package Reviewers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:42
msgid ""
"Anyone can review a PR so we encourage Spack’s community members to review "
"and comment on those involving software in which they have expertise and/or "
"interest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:44
msgid ""
"As a Package Reviewer, you are **expected** to assess changes in PRs to the "
"best of your ability and knowledge with special consideration to the "
"information contained in the :ref:`package-review-guide`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:49
msgid "Maintainers (Package Owners)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:51
msgid ""
"Maintainers are individuals (technically GitHub accounts) who appear in a "
"package’s :ref:`maintainers` directive. These are people who have agreed to "
"be notified of and given the opportunity to review changes to packages. They "
"are, from a Spack package perspective, `Code Owners <https://docs.github.com/"
"en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-"
"your-repository/about-code-owners>`_ of the package, whether or not they "
"“own” or work on the software that the package builds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:55
msgid "As a Maintainer, you are **expected**, when available, to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:57
msgid ""
"review PRs in a timely manner (reported in :ref:`committers`) to confirm "
"that the changes made to the package are reasonable;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:58
msgid "confirm that packages successfully build on at least one platform; and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:59
msgid "attempt to confirm that any updated or included tests pass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:61
msgid ""
"See :ref:`build_success_reviews` for acceptable forms of build success "
"confirmation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:65
msgid ""
"If at least one maintainer approves a PR -– and there are no objections from "
"others -– then the PR can be merged by any of the :ref:`committers`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:70
msgid "Committers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:72
msgid ""
"Committers are vetted individuals who are allowed to merge PRs into the "
"``develop`` branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:74
msgid "As a Committer, you are **expected** to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:76
msgid ""
"ensure **at least one review** is performed prior to merging (GitHub rules "
"enforce this);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:77
msgid ""
"encourage **at least one** :ref:`Package Maintainer <package-maintainers>` "
"(if any) to comment and/or review the PR;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:78
msgid ""
"allow Package Maintainers (if any) **up to one week** to comment or provide "
"a review;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:79
msgid ""
"determine if the criteria defined in :ref:`package-review-guide` are met; and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:80
msgid "**merge the reviewed PR** at their discretion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:84
msgid ""
"If there are no :ref:`package-maintainers` or the Maintainers have not "
"commented or reviewed the PR within the allotted time, you will need to "
"conduct the review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:88
msgid "The following criteria must be met in order to become a Committer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:90
msgid "cannot be an anonymous account;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:91
msgid "must come from a known and trustworthy organization;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:92
msgid "demonstrated record of contribution to Spack;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:93
msgid "have an account on the Spack Slack workspace;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:94
msgid "be approved by the Onboarding subcommittee; and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../roles_and_responsibilities.rst:95
msgid "(proposed) be known to at least 3 members of the core development team."
msgstr ""
